        "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nOn the Portfolio page, when toggling to dark mode, the logo text renders as grey, making it difficult to see against the dark background. Similarly, the texts in the client testimonials section also appear grey, reducing visibility and negatively impacting UI/UX.\n\n### To Reproduce\n\nTo Reproduce\n\n1. Navigate to the Portfolio page from the Home page.\n2. Toggle the site to dark mode.\n3. Observe that the logo text appears grey.\n4. Scroll to the client testimonials section and note that the texts also render as grey.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIn dark mode, the logo text and all client testimonial texts should render in white (or a bright color with sufficient contrast) to ensure visibility and maintain proper UI/UX.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
